  "prompt": "What are the good ways to mirror the uv's in maya?",
  "response": "Here are several good methods to mirror UVs in Maya:\n\n1. UV Editor Mirror Commands\n- UV > Mirror (with options for X, Y, or Z axis)\n- Provides direct, simple mirroring\n\n2. UV Editing Tools\n- Select UVs\n- Use Transform tools (Move, Rotate, Scale)\n- Hold down 'V' key for precise mirroring\n\n3. Symmetry Mode\n- In UV Editor, enable Symmetry Mode\n- Allows real-time symmetric editing\n- Useful for more complex UV adjustments\n\n4. Maya's Reflection Tool\n- Select UVs\n- Use Edit UVs > Symmetrize\n- Choose reflection axis and plane\n\n5. Script/Hotkey Methods\n- Create custom scripts for quick mirroring\n- Assign keyboard shortcuts for faster workflow\n\n6. Transfer UV Method\n- Use Transfer Maps tool\n- Can help mirror UVs between similar meshes\n\nPro Tips:\n- Ensure pivot/center point is correctly positioned\n- Check for overlapping UVs after mirroring\n- Use UDIM workflow for complex mirroring scenarios\n\nRecommended approach depends on specific UV layout and symmetry requirements.",
